flowRoot.flowPara: Here, abstraction refers to the process of finding the most pertinant feature(s) of an entity within the current context, and generalising it beyond the specifc case. We start with a single description of a specific protocol (preferably one we believe is good) and generalise the key or essential features for many cases.

flowRoot.flowPara: There are many features of sodium azide we could focus on - e.g.1) it is a colourless sodium salt, 2) it has a molecular weight of 275oC, or 3) it is often used as a gas forming agent in car airbag systems. However, the important aspect in this context is its effect as an inhibitor of bacterial growth.
We abstract this particular feature and make it an independent object of thought that can be (re)applied to other cases or systems.
